<br>
But I think we as wizards should do a better job of &quot;selling&quot; ourselves has one of the more valuable additions to a standard experience group.  I think many players are locked into the kunark/velious view of wizards.  VI could do us a huge favor by broadcasting our damage to the group but that seems it'll never happen.  So we need to really start spreading the word that with a horse/kei/ft items/aa we are the #1 (or #2) sustained damage dealing class.  And groups are not optimal exp-ing without us!<br>
<br>
There is a large faulty bias out there and we need to fight it with facts. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;">|</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=187364"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;">C</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">ASTAA</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.guildhouse.net/veturi/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;">&lt;V</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">ETURI</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:small;">&gt;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;"> | </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">65 - SAGE WIZARD</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;"> | </span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:x-small;">FENNIN RO</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:medium;"> |</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elfindrol>Elfindrol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/13/02 2:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wiz LFGing</span><hr size=1> I play two characters, a wizard, and a chanter. The wiz is 52 and the chanter is 59... I consider the wiz my Main as I enjoy it the most[1].<br>
<br>
I have the same personality behind both characters. When I'm on the chanter, I can set LFG and get at *least* 1 invite within a minute or so.. normally 2-3.<br>
<br>
The chanter doesn't even have to be LFG.. I get regular invites from folk I've grouped with in the past.<br>
<br>
The Wizard... I solo. I solo with LFG on. People don't go /who all wizard lfg, but they do /who all enchanter lfg.<br>
<br>
A good personality, friends in game, and a history of quality grouping will get you a group as a wizard.<br>
<br>
For many of the other classes, all that is required is that tag that says &quot;enchanter&quot; or &quot;cleric.&quot;<br>
<br>
On the wiz if I get in a bad group, I deal with it.. because I'm in a group! On the chanter, if I am uncomfy with the group composition, I can politely disband, set LFG, and get a new composition within a few moments.<br>
<br>
At the base level, there is a problem.. but that problem is simple... we aren't a buffing class or a melee class. Encahnters, mages, and druids are all magic users who aren't primary/alternate melee that provide buffs.<br>
<br>
Melee's do melee well.. Hybrids can be viewed as a melee with extra casting.<br>
<br>
Wizards, we are pure casters and that's that. Perception is what it is. Wizards are NOT as groupable as the other classes.<br>
<br>
Again, just my edumacated opinion from playing multiple classes.<br>
<br>
-E <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=claudshadowflare>ClaudShadowflare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>Has Eddie Murphy's<BR>taste in women</span><br>  Posts: 1691<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/13/02 2:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wiz LFGing</span><hr size=1> Hey, look at this, it's time for our daily &quot;I can't find a group because I just put up my LFG flag and cry for 2 hours, we need work!&quot; post.  Allow me to get out my deadhorse beating club one more time.<br>
<br>
Perception always trumps reality.  If people thought rogues were lousy damage dealers without the ability to CC or offer other benefits to their group- regardless of the truth- they'd have problems finding groups.  The key is proving you're a damn good player, by-<br>
<br>
a) Knowing how and when to use all your spells; when it's right to use a rain (PoV is a surprisingly good zone for rains when you have a shaman/mage/druid around), when it's right to use a large nuke vs. a draught, when you should stun, etc.<br>
b) FORMING groups.  Doesn't have to be a slower/healer/tank/mana/dmg/dmg group, I was in a FAST 3wiz/3mag group last night, be creative.  When you form your own groups, people tend to remember you and start inviting you to their groups.<br>
c) Having a clue how to play your class.  Based on some of the arguments some wizards post against their class, I'm beginning to wonder how serious of a problem this is.  We've got people here saying wizards can't provide high burst DPS and aren't wanted on PoP raids, and when shit like that starts getting stirred (think of it as saying people would rather have a ranger tanking than a warrior), one has to get concerned about their brethren.<br>
<br>
Do that and you'll find groups. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://mysite.verizon.net/vze1k2wt/sig1.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elasto>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 920<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/13/02 2:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wiz LFGing</span><hr size=1> Well, I can comment as I am that 'other class' that people look for.<br>
<br>
Yes, of course I get tells. I may well get a tell the minute I set lfg. If I dont I probably wont get one for a while though.<br>
<br>
Honestly, the only classes I know that get tells with any sort of regularity from strangers are clerics and chanters. I have a shaman friend who gets tells, but not as often as I do. Our guild warrior MT (who is nicely equipped indeed) complains in guild after spending another hour lfg with no tells.<br>
<br>
It's really a huge myth that any of the other classes get more tells for pickup groups than wizards do. And we can solo for group level xp while we wait, which hardly any other class can do. And wizards can fill 3 spots in a group whereas clerics, chanters and plate tanks are each fighting for a single spot (more if you'll go unconventional).<br>
<br>
Repeat after me:<br>
<br>
The only people in EQ that get fast pickup groups day after day are .. the ones that start them!<br>
<br>
