<br>
We have BoF and high agro generating spells.  Snare, nuke, run, nuke, run, nuke, etc, and all the while the melee is beating the crap outta the mob (which he can easily keep up with, as it is snared) while taking no damage himself.  His &quot;uptime&quot; increases incredibly.  Other caster classes are less desirable as a melee's partner because much of their damage is pet generated, meaning the actual caster doesnt hold agro quite so well, and mostly they don't have a snare effect either.<br>
<br>
Melees (or hybrids) are great partners for wizards because, aside from their own damage generation, they allow us to use mana more efficiently* AND meditate more**.  They also are very nice to have about in case of adds.  With a melee partner, I dont have to channel or run a long ways to scrape off an add.<br>
<br>
*The melee partner can finish off mobs in the &quot;fleeing&quot; stage, meaning I dont have to cast a 700 dmg nuke to do those last 400 hp, or use a lower dmg/mana ratio spell as a finisher.<br>
<br>
**The melee can do the grunt work of going and finding things to kill while I meditate.  Also, since I dont have to finish the mob, I can med an extra tick or two or three at the end of each fight.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hybrids often bring useful spells of their own as well.  Healing, faster than boot SoW, Snare, what have you.<br>
<br>
<br>
