LOL that's baloney.  In fact when I wrote that post I actually deleted the second paragraph, which was about my necro's personal favorite partner, the beastlord.  When I login with the intention of grouping, the first thing I do is /who all beastlord 50-60.  Purity, SOW, chloro, slow and a nice pet make them the necro's best option IMO.  The only disadvantage to BST is that most of them play goodie races, which eliminates some of my favorite camps.  <br>
<br>
As for other classes, sorry but I never see wiz suggested especially since PoP came out.  The only time people even mentioned wizards was if there were some kind of stipulation like their friend was a wizard or wanted to play a wizard and they wanted some feedback on whether it would work.<br>
<br>
Hybrids usually go with enchanter for buffs, slow, CC heck a gazillion things.  Pure melee pretty much always go with shaman while druids and clerics have always been popular choices.  All pet classes like teaming up though I think necro should always be half of the equation if just for fearkiting and undead slows plus CC.  Skilled enchanters like the druid's 10-minute snare, plus SOW and track for hellacious charm killing.<br>
<br>
