Folks, EVERY class is going to have a streak of not being able to get a group.  In my guild during PoP that's been equally true among the int casters, healers, and melees.  The most bitching I've heard on this subject seems to be coming from the few sub-60s we have left on the roster, and that shouldn't be really surprising as PoP was designed really for a post-60s crowd.<br>
You aren't being singled out unless you're significantly lower than the average person in the zone.  Shoot, I just had my first experience group in ages myself last night.  Most nights-- if I'm not raiding or helping people to get keyed-- I'm soloing in PoN in between rounds of zoning into other places/telling the guild I'm LFG.  Or working on trade skills. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
